React Error #185 "Maximum update depth exceeded" SUCCESSFULLY RESOLVED in NewPostDialog component. Final fix was memoizing function props to prevent infinite re-renders:

**Root Cause (Final)**: 
- Unmemoized function prop `onImagesChange={(urls) => handleInputChange("images", urls)}` in NewPostDialog.tsx created new function on every render
- This caused ImageUpload component's useEffect to trigger infinite re-renders due to changing dependency

**Final Solution Applied**:
```typescript
const handleInputChange = React.useCallback((
  field: keyof z.infer<typeof createPostSchema>,
  value: string | string[],
) => {
  setForm((prev) => ({ ...prev, [field]: value }));
  if (touched[field]) {
    validateField(field, value);
  }
}, [touched]);

const handleImagesChange = React.useCallback((urls: string[]) => {
  handleInputChange("images", urls);
}, [handleInputChange]);
```

**Testing Results**:
- Page loads successfully without console errors
- Clicking post creation button opens dialog successfully
- No React Error #185 in console
- Only expected warnings (auth 401, missing descriptions) remain

**All Previous Issues Also Fixed**:
- Duplicate setIsDialogOpen calls
- Duplicate onClose calls 
- Object dependencies in useEffect
- Missing handlePostRemoved function
- Conditional rendering cycles

Dialog now opens properly and functions correctly without infinite loops.
